	   SPELL=kover
         VERSION=0.8.3
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://lisas.de/kover/$SOURCE
        WEB_SITE=http://lisas.de/kover
         ENTERED=20020216
         UPDATED=20020311
      MAINTAINER=mtzanidakis@yahoo.com
           SHORT="An easy to use WYSIWYG CD cover printer with CDDB support."
cat << EOF
Kover is an easy to use WYSIWYG CD cover printer with CDDB support.
Features :
o CDDB support via freedb.org
o Supports proxies with authentification
o Image embedding in inlet and booklet
o Should read files saved with Easy CD Pro 2.0
o Saves CDDB queries locally, and uses them next time the same CD is inserted.
o Print to file or printer (surprising?)
o Able to save and load with kover created covers
o Save and load files via ftp
o Do CDDB query without the CD. Just enter the ID and category
o French, german and norwegian translation available
EOF

